      "span_text": "The most extreme situations are found in some poriferan species, Cnidaria, Chaetognatha and the green algae Pseudendoclonium akinetum, which have retained only one or two mitochondrial tRNA genes, and in the trypanosomatids and apicomplexans that lack mitochondrial tRNA genes altogether"
